Given:
Temperature = 300 K
Avogadro’s number (N_A) = 6.02 × 10^23 atoms/g-atom
Density of silicon (ρ) = 2.33 × 10^6 g/m^3
Atomic weight of silicon = 28.1
Intrinsic carrier concentration (n_i) = 1.5 × 10^16 m^-3
Electron mobility (μ_n) = 0.14 m^2/V·s
Hole mobility (μ_p) = 0.05 m^2/V·s
Charge of electron (q) = 1.6 × 10^-19 C

--------------------------------------------------
STEP 1: Number of silicon atoms per m³

Number of gram-atoms per m³
= Density / Atomic weight
= (2.33 × 10^6) / 28.1
= 8.29 × 10^4 g-atoms/m³

Number of silicon atoms per m³
= (8.29 × 10^4) × (6.02 × 10^23)
= 4.99 × 10^28 atoms/m³

--------------------------------------------------
STEP 2: Number of electron-hole pairs per m³

For intrinsic semiconductor:
Number of electrons = Number of holes = n_i

Electron-hole pairs per m³
= n_i
= 1.5 × 10^16 pairs/m³

--------------------------------------------------
STEP 3: Relative concentration of silicon atoms

Relative concentration
= (Number of Si atoms) / (Number of electron-hole pairs)

= (4.99 × 10^28) / (1.5 × 10^16)
= 3.33 × 10^12

--------------------------------------------------
STEP 4: Conductivity of intrinsic silicon

σ = q × n_i × (μ_n + μ_p)

σ = (1.6 × 10^-19) × (1.5 × 10^16) × (0.14 + 0.05)
σ = (1.6 × 10^-19) × (1.5 × 10^16) × 0.19
σ = 4.56 × 10^-4 S/m

--------------------------------------------------
STEP 5: Intrinsic resistivity of silicon

ρ = 1 / σ
ρ = 1 / (4.56 × 10^-4)
ρ ≈ 2193 Ω·m

--------------------------------------------------
FINAL ANSWERS:

Relative concentration of silicon atoms
= 3.33 × 10^12

Intrinsic resistivity of silicon
≈ 2.19 × 10^3 Ω·m
